{{Quote|In our efforts, we have learned that life is not rare. Rather, given a chance, ''life will occur''. It is tenacious, aggressive&mdash;it seems to crave existence.|Tem Eliss, [[Sentientologist]]|<ref name="GG12" />}}
[[Professor/Legends|Professor]] '''Tem Eliss''' was an [[Iyra]] [[sentientologist]] who worked in the [[University of Sanbra]]'s [[Sentient Studies Department]]. His [[Book/Legends|book]], ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life]]'', was considered too pro-[[Alien/Legends|alien]] for [[Commission for the Preservation of the New Order/Legends|COMPNOR]], and made him a fugitive from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. It was rumored that he went on to join a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] cell.

==Biography==
===Early career===
Tem Eliss was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Iyra]]<ref name="GG12" /> who was a native of his [[Species/Legends|species']] [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[F'tral]], although he was raised among the [[Star/Legends|stars]] rather than in the oceans and was not immersed in Iyra culture. Largely as a result of his upbringing, Eliss was unlike most of his kind; he spent decades studying [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] species and their cultures,<ref name="J14" /> becoming a noted [[Scholar/Legends|scholar]]<ref name="G3">{{GamerCite|3|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Jawas}}</ref> and one of the most respected and well-known [[sentientologist]]s in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. Eliss eventually became the head of the [[Sentient Studies Department]] of the [[University of Sanbra]].<ref name="J14" /> Known as a demanding but fair teacher, Eliss was one of the most popular instructors within his department and had an office on the university's campus.<ref name="GG12" />

At one point, Eliss, then a [[Professor/Legends|professor]], was operating out of the [[Cultural Studies Department]] of the [[Advora]] [[Advora Learning Center|Learning Center]] on [[Riflor/Legends|Riflor]] when the city was struck by one of the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] frequent [[Groundquake/Legends|earthquakes]]. Eliss, who had only been on Riflor for a few weeks, was en route from the other side of the planet at the time of the earthquake; his [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] was commandeered to search for survivors, and the academic found himself participating in the relief effort, serving as an emergency [[Medic/Legends|medic]]. In the process, Eliss gained many insights into the culture and personalities of the [[Advozse/Legends|Advozsec]].<ref name="G4">{{GamerCite|4|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Advozsec}}</ref>

===Fugitive from the Empire===
Eliss became infamous for his disregard of the protocols of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and he landed in trouble for anti-Imperial rhetoric on more than one occasion. This came to a boiling point when, upon the request of the faculty, Eliss was preparing ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life]]'',<ref name="J14" /> which he intended as an aid to travelers, merchants, and others who frequently came into contact with new cultures and species. Eliss believed that achieving his goal for the document required him to honestly state facts without regard for their [[Politics/Legends|political]] implications;<ref name="GG12" /> the ''Guide'' deviated significantly from the doctrines of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and included findings that criticized Imperial policies regarding sentient rights.<ref name="G3" /> [[Commission for the Preservation of the New Order/Legends|COMPNOR]] loyalists on Professor Eliss' staff notified COMPNOR [[Sanbra sector/Legends|Sanbra sector]] monitor [[Bront Autin]] of the impending publication of the guide and its failure to adhere to Imperial doctrine, and Autin recommended detaining and questioning Eliss to COMPNOR [[Executive Director]] [[Kem Tija]].<ref name="GG12" />

Eliss ultimately made his ''Guide'' available on public channels before fleeing the university to avoid imprisonment for releasing data deemed inappropriate by the Empire,<ref name="G1" /> taking all of his research material with him.<ref name="GG12" /> As Eliss fled [[Sanbra]], Professor [[Mankuskett]] and a [[Changeling/Legends|changeling]] in the guise of a [[Nikto/Legends|Nikto]] accompanied him away from the campus to the quiet landing pads south of the [[Shoapy Hostel]], where a squad of COMPNOR officers blocked the roadway. By impersonating a [[Human/Legends|Human]] Imperial officer, the changeling moved Eliss and Mankuskett through the roadblock and to their ship.<ref name="G10">{{GamerCite|10|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Clawdites}}</ref> COMPNOR officials detained several students for questioning in an apparent attempt to determine whether Eliss harbored any sympathies toward the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], although all were released within hours.<ref name="GG12" />

Thirty-seven Sanbra [[Standard hour/Legends|hours]] after his escape, the fugitive Eliss arrived at a [[Priapulin]] colony on [[Krinemonen III]], a small outpost in the [[Mon Calamari Shipyards/Legends|Mon Calamari Shipyards]].<ref name="G8">{{GamerCite|8|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Priapulin}}</ref> Eliss slowly disseminated ''The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life'' through the [[HoloNet/Legends|HoloNet]]<ref name="G3" /> from his hidden place of exile<ref name="G1" /> on Krinemonen III,<ref name="G10" /> and the ''Guide'' began appearing on student [[Datanet/Legends|communication nets]] three weeks after his disappearance.<ref name="GG12" /> Eliss' publication of the first draft of the ''Guide'' shocked the academic community and attracted attention from fellow scholars, as well as from proponents of free speech.<ref name="G3" /> The renegade Eliss transmitted at least one entry of the ''Guide'' from a HoloNet node in [[Hutt Space/Legends|Hutt Space]], where he was believed to have studied all of the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] servant races to test his theories concerning Hutt genetic and cultural manipulation.<ref name="G6">{{GamerCite|6|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Nikto}}</ref> It was also rumored that Eliss established contact with a Rebel Alliance cell and joined the group.<ref name="GG12" />

===Later life===
Eliss was still alive after the signing of the [[Pellaeon–Gavrisom Treaty|peace accords]] between the [[Imperial Remnant]] and the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], and he revealed the details of his escape from Sanbra into temporary exile 25 years after said escape.<ref name="G10" /> By the time of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]], Eliss had returned to Sanbra, where he witnessed a [[Nosaurian/Legends|Nosaurian]] aide's reaction to news that her [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] had been devastated by the Vong.<ref name="G9">{{GamerCite|9|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Nosaurians}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
Tem Eliss was a gifted scholar and an amiable being, unlike most Iyra; the species possessed a reputation for being egotistical, condescending, and obnoxious. Many representatives of Iyra culture disliked Eliss for keeping company with members of other species.<ref name="J14" />

